JOHANNESBURG - The economy appears to be growing despite last month's VAT increase. BankServAfrica’s economic transaction index (BETI) was 2.8 percent higher than in the same period last year. READ: World Bank raises SA's 2018 economic growth forecast Although slightly lower compared with March’s year-on-year growth of 3 percent, April 2018’s figure still shows the strength of the economy at the start of the second quarter. The BETI transactions monitor declined slightly in April to 96.9-million from a record set in March of 101 million transactions. eNCA